                                                                <customfield id="customfield_12310192" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Release Note</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>This patch replaces the default jersey json marshaller/unmarshaller with jackson. It updates unit tests to include json serialization/deserialization verification. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The patch is backward compatible except for the following:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
StorageClusterStatusModel, which is broken and had to be fixed in this patch. It only shows one node in the liveNodes field.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Previously when submitting requests represented in json, some fields prefixed with the &amp;#39;@&amp;#39; sign were accepted as equivalent to the same field name without the prefix. This was unintended and likely caused by a bug in Jersey. This has been rectified and no longer supported. It should be noted that responses represented in json remain the same (no &amp;#39;@&amp;#39; prefix).&lt;br/&gt;
</customfieldvalue>

